The New Technology Stack


Competition
Visual
James E. Heppelmann Michael E. Porter




Smart, connected products require companies to build and support an entirely new technology infrastructure. This “technology stack” is made up of multiple layers, including new product hardware, embedded software, connectivity, a product cloud consisting of software running on remote servers, a suite of security tools, a gateway for external information services, and integration with enterprise business systems.


